WEBVTT

00:08:29.920 --> 00:08:33.176
you can't fast-forward in those things.

00:08:33.200 --> 00:08:36.336
What do you see as the future
of those for storytelling?

00:08:36.360 --> 00:08:39.096
SR: I spent a lot of time in the past year

00:08:39.120 --> 00:08:40.696
just exploring those,

00:08:40.720 --> 00:08:43.376
getting lots of demonstrations
and paying attention.

00:08:43.400 --> 00:08:45.216
I find them fascinating,

00:08:45.240 --> 00:08:47.216
mainly because I think that --

00:08:47.240 --> 00:08:49.536
I think most people
think of them for gaming,

00:08:49.560 --> 00:08:52.256
I think most people think of them
for things like action,

00:08:52.280 --> 00:08:54.936
and I think that there is
a sense of intimacy

00:08:54.960 --> 00:08:58.856
that is very present in those things,

00:08:58.880 --> 00:09:01.376
the idea that -- picture this,